Exploratory Data Analysis¶

1. Objective of the Proposed Research:¶

Project Objective: To gather teams that are best suited to preparing assignment reports and projects that match compatibility's and interests. During the project, students analyze their area of interest and their major.

The project provides recommendations for grouping the teams together for students who have interests in similar areas, and they work on the project collaboratively. These students have a variety of skill sets that they can use together, so they can learn from each other as well.

In the project, the professors will receive recommendations on groups of teams based on the points they earned on their last assignment and their project score. This will enable them to assign advanced tasks and identify students who need closer supervision.

Ultimately, we create groups of students based on their purpose is to determine team members.

Stakeholder - Canvas Tool - (https://www.instructure.com/canvas)

Our stakeholder is Canvas, an interactive tool that has feature to help students group together and choose the teamates that could provide better suggestions to the students to join the group and work together. Similarly, the clustering algorithms used can also help the professor to put together the based on their performance level and interests and ccompatibilty. This is instead of putting together random students or manually recognizing students to make the team.

6. Step-by-step hierarchical clustering¶

Hierarchical Label encoding¶

The idea that interests, majors, and employment types are correlated is applied. And they are all categorical so label encoded data were used for hierarchical clustering. All categorical values have converted into an integer value as below.

#### Leave-One-Out Encoding (LOO Encoding)
import category_encoders as ce
loo_encoder = ce.LeaveOneOutEncoder(cols=['INTERESTED_PROJECT_AREA', 'AGE_GROUP', 'EMPLOYMENT_TYPE', 'FORMAL_EDUCATION', 'UNDERGRAD_MAJOR', 'MAJOR_CATEGORY', 'COUNTRY'], sigma=0.05)
loo_encoder.fit(df, list(range(0, 100)))
X_encoded = loo_encoder.transform(df)

X_sel = X_encoded[['INTERESTED_PROJECT_AREA', 'UNDERGRAD_MAJOR', 'EMPLOYMENT_TYPE']]; X_sel.head()

def kModesClustering(inputDataset, method = 'Huang'):

    clusters = kmodes.fit_predict(inputDataset)
    return clusters

cost = []

    kmode = KModes(n_clusters=num_clusters, init = "random", n_init = 5, verbose=1);
    kmode.fit_predict(df_modes_new);
    cost.append(kmode.cost_);

# Your function returns the classification of your data-point
def kNN(kNN_df, input_point):
    X_var = kNN_df[['Assignment_1st', 'Assignment_2nd', 'Assignment_3rd']].values
    y_var = kNN_df['Class'].values
    
    # X_var = StandardScaler().fit(X_var).transform(X_var.astype(float))

    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_var, y_var, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 0)

    k = 5

    neigh = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = k)
    neigh.fit(X_train, y_train)

    yhat = neigh.predict(X_test)
    err = round(accuracy_score(y_test, yhat)*100, 2)
    
    classification_point = neigh.predict(pd.DataFrame(input_point, index= [i for i in range(len(d))]))
    return classification_point

11. Project Report¶

10 paragraphs and a few plots. Your report should be addressed to your stakeholder and the analysis should be relevant to them.¶

Our motive behind this project is that students can find others who can be their best versions as a project partner¶

The focal point of our project is to club students in such a way that working in a project in fact increases their productivity. Our Stakeholer Canvas, is a Learning Management System (LMS portal) that is used by universities to help students focus on education rather than simply understanding how to navigate the system. It allows both students and professors to keep track of how the subjects are progressing. We would like to suggest the Machine Learning Clustering Algorithm to help sort students into appropriate teams so that they can achieve a productive result.

Our dataset consists of categorical and numerical values which are needed for our clustering model to club students based on interests and assignments and project scores. If we check below we can see the different areas that students are interested and also the scores they secured in assignments and projects

Originality¶

No other similar published works for clustering found with similar dataset" specified¶

Our project is completely original and one-of-a-kind because we don't just group students based on their assignment or project scores, but also on their interests. We created our dataset from scratch and did not use any pre-existing datasets. Because we wanted to use a categorical and numerical value as our decider in grouping students, the cleaning too is done with encoding methods. We chose CANVAS as our stakeholder because it is the platform used by universities in the United States, and because university modules are posted on Canvas, professors could use our model to group students on the same platform as well.We haven't seen any similar published clustering work done with the dataset used in our project.
